OL,5, An organisation representing Scottish  
OL,6, sports writers has apologised after an 
OL,7, awards event speech prompted a walkout.
OL,9,FTV presenter Eilidh Barbour was among  
OL,10,Fguests who left Sunday's Scottish      
OL,11,FFootball Writers' Association (SFWA)   
OL,12,Fgala dinner in Glasgow in protest.     
OL,14,FMs Barbour tweeted that she had "never 
OL,15,Ffelt so unwelcome in the industry"     
OL,16,Fwhile others have described the jokes  
OL,17,F"sexist, racist and homophobic".       
OL,19,FThe SFWA said it apologised to anyone  
OL,20,F"offended or upset" by the speech.     
